sentences: Phil Waldorf (born 1974) is an American music industry executive.
After moving to Brooklyn, New York, from Athens in 1998, Waldorf worked at the record store Other Music.
In 1999, Waldorf became founding label manager of independent record label Misra; as the public face of the label, which was under other ownership, he headed its operations and A&R until 2006.
